<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-466] Cannot load log4j2 config file if path contains plus &apos;+&apos; characters</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-466</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hello,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I was trying to programmatically load a XML config file from the temporary data directory of a MacOS X system. The temp path consists of serveral &apos;&amp;#43;&apos; characters like MacOS automatically generates this path so we have to take it this way. Even I would agree that it is not nice to have &apos;&amp;#43;&apos; chars in a path name.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I tried to load the XML config the framework permanently loaded the DefaultConfig and not the desired XML configuration.&lt;br/&gt;
By stepping through the debugger I figured out that this was caused by the method fileFromURI() in org.apache.logging.log4j.core.helpers.FileUtils.java .&lt;br/&gt;
The misbehaviour was basically caused by the call of URL.decode() which converts &apos;+&apos; to &apos; &apos; (space) of a given String. &lt;br/&gt;
Now I self-compiled the whole framework without the call of URL.decode() and the XML configuration loaded properly. &lt;br/&gt;
I can not see why this call is necessary in this method so in my opinion this should be removed.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Kind regards&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Mac Pro &lt;/p&gt;</environment>
